fields.name: Walking food tasting trail in Valetta
fields.short_description: Enjoy a taste of Malta’s capital city. Visit some of the local artisans crafting traditional food and drinks on the tiny island nation.
fields.full_description: Enjoy a taste of Malta’s capital city of Valletta on this walking tour. Visit some of the local artisans crafting traditional food and drinks on the tiny island nation. This tour will give you the opportunity to sample Maltese cheese, chocolates, sweet and savoury pastries, plus locally brewed beer and regional wine. Spend a leisurely morning sampling the delights of Maltese cuisine Enjoy a variety of hand-crafted treats, wine, and beer Tour is limited to 14 participants. Reserve your spot and don’t miss out Due to the nature of the tour, food sensitivities can’t be accommodated
fields.included: Beverages, food tasting, light refreshments, snacks, professional guide, coffee and/or Tea, Alcoholic Beverages
fields.departure_location: Triq San Gwann, Il-Belt Valletta, Malta The guide will be in front of the main entrance of St John's Co Cathedral in St John's Square, Valletta. Opposite the entrance to Zachary Street. Do NOT go to the visitor's entrance in Republic Street.

fields.name: Ta'Mena Wine Tours
fields.short_description: You will discover the history of winemaking in the Maltese Islands, followed by a visit to our vineyards, olive grove and small animal farm.
fields.full_description:
At Ta’ Mena Wine Estate a typical wine tour starts with a historical introduction of winemaking in the Maltese Islands and the estate itself, followed by a visit to our vineyards, olive grove and small animal farm. The tour can also be extended to our winery which is only three minutes away by car. Visitors will be given the opportunity to taste the different wines produced in our boutique winery, as well as purchase them from our onsite retail outlets.
Throughout the wine tour visitors will be guided by our wine expert who will give first-hand information about our viticulture methods, detailed information about our wines, the process of winemaking and how one should taste wine to understand and enjoy it better.  The wine tasting sessions are also accompanied by some of our typical pres
fields.included: All taxes, fees and handling charges, wine tasting, food tasting, professional guide,
fields.what_to_bring: Sun hut, sun screen, comfortable shoes and spending money
fields.departure_location: Ta’ Mena Estate and at Ta’ Mena Experience in Xewkija, Gozo

fields.name: Blue Grotto and Marsaxlokk Half-Day Tour from Valletta
fields.short_description: The magnificent Blue Grotto and the lively fishing village of Marsaxlokk are two of Malta’s most popular attractions and this morning tour from Valletta visits both. Set sail on a small boat cruise around the stunning sea caves, then head to Marsaxlokk to browse the market and admire the views.
fields.full_description: The magnificent Blue Grotto and the lively fishing village of Marsaxlokk are two of Malta’s most popular attractions and this morning tour from Valletta visits both. Set sail on a small boat cruise around the stunning sea caves, then head to Marsaxlokk to browse the market and admire the colorful ‘luzzu’ fishing boats. Half-day Blue Grotto and Marsaxlokk Tour from Valletta Cruise around the Blue Grotto, one of Malta’s most visited natural wonders Browse the local market in Marsaxlokk and stroll around the atmospheric fishing port Ideal tour for first-time visitors to Malta or those short on time
fields.included: Stop At:   Marsaxlokk Bay Visit the fishing village of Marsaxlokk where free time to stroll around the market will be allowed. Duration: 1 hour  Admission Ticket Free Stop At:   Blue Grotto (Il-Hnejja) Picturesque Blue Grotto Duration: 30 minutes Admission Ticket Free Stop At:   Blue Grotto (Il-Hnejja) Weather permitting we shall take a boat to the Grotto to view the magnificent underwater flora. (boat fare not included)

fields.name: Fishing Day Charter
fields.short_description: If you enjoy fishing with friends and family and would love the opportunity to visit the best spots within our Maltese Territorial waters and have the chance to catch local fish then this trip is for you! Both on-shore and off-shore fishing are possible options.
fields.full_description: If you enjoy fishing with friends and family and would love the opportunity to visit the best spots within our Maltese Territorial waters and have the chance to catch local fish then this trip is for you! Both on-shore and off-shore fishing are possible options. Depending on the season, the following fish is what you can expect to catch! Bream, Wrasse, Comber, Mullet, Parrot-fish, Amberjack, Barracuda, Albacore Tuna, Skipjack, Dentex, Dorado to name a few..
fields.included: Lunch, alcoholic beverages, bottled water, fishing tackle and equipment, bait
fields.departure_location: ix-Xatt Ta' Xbiex, Ta' Xbiex, Malta Upon your arrival at Roland Marina, please proceed to Pontoon D where you will find the Charter Operator named Juri. Juri will be there to greet and help you board the fishing boat Lucky VII. Chris will be your designated Fishing Skipper Guide for the entire trip.

fields.name: Fishing Trips Malta and Gozo
fields.short_description: Fishing Mania organizes fishing charters that take up to six people for a full day and night fishing trip. However, four clients per trip are recommended for the best comfort. Fishing trips are done with the 27 feet long Bayliner Trophy.
fields.full_description: Malta is one of the greatest places on earth for clean sea, nice people and good fishing. Take an exciting offshore big game charter for serious fish like bluefin tuna, Albacore, Dorado (lampuki) and for the mysterious night bottom fishing for snapper, grouper squid and many more. Which certainly will make you return year after year for great times? Our qualified captains and staff that know these waters will take you to the best migratory paths for serious fishing. The price includes a fully equipped Bayliner Trophy with the best fishing gear for the targeted species, The boat is equipped with all the best safety features, packed lunch drinks and finally good company. All our fishing is done near the island of Gozo, so if you stay in Malta, we can pick you from Cirkewwa near the ferry

fields.name: St Paul's Bay: Blue Lagoon, Beaches & Bays Trip by Catamaran
fields.short_description: Board a modern sailing catamaran and set off on a lively boat tour along the coast. Go swimming in crystal clear waters, listen to dance music on board, and enjoy an optional BBQ.
fields.full_description: After boarding the catamaran, the first stop will be the Blue Lagoon. The boat will drop anchor away from the crowds, so you can experience the famous turquoise water in peace. During this stop, you can enjoy an optional barbecue. The stops after the Blue Lagoon will depend on the weather. It might be possible to head to the Crystal Lagoon, surrounded by steep dramatic cliffs. Its crystal clear waters are much deeper than the Blue Lagoon, making the area fantastic for snorkelling and swimming in and around the caves. If there is an easterly wind, it’s likely that you’ll visit Ghajn Tuffieha. This is a beautiful rural area, home to a chain of pristine sandy beaches called Golden Bay, Riviera Beach, and Gnejna Bay. On the way back, we will discover the film set of Popeye’s Village.
fields.included: Transportation by catamaran, Expert Crew onboard, use of snorkelling equipment (£10 cash deposit onboard), barbecue
fields.what_to_bring: Sunglasses, sun hat, swimwear, towel, sunscreen, cash
fields.departure_location: Meet at the Sea Adventure desk at Bugibba Harbor • Look for a guide wearing GetYourGuide attire and holding a red GetYourGuide flag • Please arrive 45 minutes before the scheduled departure time. Boarding closes 15 minutes before departure. If you arrive after this, you will not be able to board the boat

fields.name: Malta: Gozo, Comino and The Blue Lagoon Boat Trip
fields.short_description: Discover Malta's quieter, smaller neighboring islands, Gozo and Comino. Dive into the crystal-clear waters from the onboard diving platform. Sunbathe, snorkel, or relax on the boat. Explore the Caves around Comino Island.
fields.full_description: Discover genuine Maltese charm and experience the true Malta as you cruise along the island's rugged coastline to reach Gozo and Comino Island. Your tour begins from the town of Bugibba, where your sailing boat will depart at 10:30 AM. Cruise past St. Paul's Island, Mellieha Bay, and Smuggler's Cove Cave on your way to Gozo. Upon arrival, disembark the boat and enjoy 3 hours of free time to explore the island. You may choose to take a minibus tour or simply stroll around, discovering the island's landmarks, such as caves and fishing villages, at your own pace. In the afternoon, head to Comino Island, where you can explore the island, swim near the boat or take a walk along one of the island's white sandy beaches. Head to the famous Blue Lagoon where you can snorkel in crystal-clear waters.
fields.included: Live commentary, blue Lagoon visit, Snorkeling equipment, showers, toilets, sundeck, diving platform, snack bar
fields.what_to_bring: Sunglasses, sun hat, swimwear, towel, sunscreen, cash
fields.departure_location: Bugibba Harbour, Dawret Il-Gzejjer, San Pawl il-Baħar, Malta. The vessel you will be sailing on is the only sailing boat there and is called 'Seahorse Cruises'.

fields.name: The Best Traditional 2 Harbours Day Cruise of Malta
fields.short_description: See Malta's historic cities and forts while cruising in a traditional Maltese boat. Learn about the country's history as you travel along the Grand Harbour & Marsamxett Harbour
fields.full_description: Travel long Malta's Harbours in a traditional Maltese boat. See historical forts, battlements and creeks. Experience Malta's living past at busy dockyards and marinas. This cruise leaves from Sliema Ferries. You will go around the two natural harbours and their ten creeks. A detailed, live commentary will provide you with information about the history of Valletta and the Three Cities of Senglea, Cospicua and Vittoriosa which date back to 1565. Learn about the role the three cities played in the seige of Malta during World War II. While onboard, you have access to a fully stocked bar to help you relax.

fields.name: Gozo Full-Day Jeep Tour with Lunch and Powerboat Ride
fields.short_description: See the sights of Gozo on a full-day Jeep tour and get amazing views of the landscapes and hidden corners. Visit the megalithic temple complex of Ġgantija, marvel at the salt pans and Inland Sea and much more.
fields.full_description: Explore the island of Gozo by Jeep and see the most beautiful sights in a day. Benefit from hotel pick-up in Malta and catch the ferry to Gozo, where a tour leader will meet you on arrival. Then, head to the Qala Belvedere for panoramic views across the sea. Get back to nature in the Simar Valley and visit the pretty resort town of Ramla Bay. See the ruins of a fortification built by the Knights of Malta at Calypso's Cave and explore the temple complex of Ġgantija, at your own expense. Discover the typical fishing village of Xlendi Bay, visit one of the island's oldest settlements at Kercem Heights and marvel at the rock formations of Dwejra near the Inland Sea. Get up close to the salt pans on the north coast near the popular beach resort of Marsalforn Bay.
fields.what_to_bring: Towel, face mask, hand sanitiser or tissues
fields.departure_location: Hotel pick-up and drop off, ferry tickets, lunch, 20-minute powerboat ride (weather permitting) via the Blue Lagoon and Comino Caves,

fields.name: Malta by Segway: Dingli Funtastic
fields.short_description: Enjoy a tour of Malta’s mountainous small villages and historical sites visiting picturesque cliffs and ancient tombs. Our tour guides guarantee a unique experience for your stay in Malta.
fields.full_description: A 1-hour and 45 minutes Segway tour guarantee you a unique experience whilst enjoying your stay in Malta. From the village of Dingli to the picturesque cliffs in the surrounding area, this zippy little Segway tour will give you a unique look at Malta. Surrounded by natural sites of great ecological and archaeological significance, Dingli is a quaint village in Malta’s highest area. It is a typical Maltese village and is still detached from its neighbouring communities. It is best known for its picturesque cliffs. Archaeologists trace the village back to the times of the Phoenicians and the Carthaginians, almost 2,800 years ago. The Phoenician and Carthaginian tombs were also used by the Romans, who occupied the Maltese islands way back in 218 BC.
fields.included: Helmet, elbow and knee guards, gloves tour guide, orientation session
fields.departure_location: The local supplier's office, L-Apparell, Ħad-Dingli, Malta. Transport from any location in Malta is available for a surcharge; please ask the supplier for more information.

fields.name: Stand Up Paddleboard (SUP) Yoga in Manoel Island.
fields.short_description: Come enjoy the ancient practice of Yoga combined with Stand Up Paddle Boarding! These classes take your favourite yoga routines and put them on the water!
fields.full_description:
Come enjoy the ancient practice of Yoga combined with Stand Up Paddle Boarding! These classes take your favourite yoga routines and put them on the water! Yoga practice brings balance and restores all bodily systems by creating physical, mental and spiritual harmony. Both yoga and stand up paddle boarding are great for building better balance, coordination, endurance, body strength and is great for increasing fitness and even weight loss!
No experience of yoga, SUP or SUP yoga is necessary for this class. Your certified SUP Yoga teacher Merve Yigit will guide you through a practice that starts slowly, letting you get used to the floating surface.
fields.included: SUP Yoga class is approximately 45 minutes and 45 minutes paddling around the island. In addition to this you get to have a little fun, perhaps get a little bit wet and learn to have a laugh at yourself when you get the wobbles.
fields.departure_location: Meeting point: in front of Paparazzi Restaurant, Gzira

fields.name: Kayak Gozo & Comino - Summer Rise&Shine Adventure!
fields.short_description: Skip the crowded ferry journey: travel from Gozo to Comino the slow way and take the opportunity to relax and enjoy the views as you paddle. This small-group (maximum 12) kayak tour takes you past amazing caves, bays, and rock formations and includes optional time for swim and relax.
fields.full_description: We start at Hondoq Bay and heading for the Comino tour. Please note that it may change due to weather or other factors. Here, we will set you up with the equipment and make sure you are comfortable in your kayak. You'll meet your guide and do a safety briefing. Then we set you on your way! Duration: 30 minutes Admission Ticket Free Stop At:   Blue Lagoon From the starting point in Gozo, we then kayak to Comino Island (usually about 20 minutes). Sometimes we do a short paddle along with Gozo first if you need a little time to practice!
fields.included: Use of Kayak equipment: kayak, life vest, paddle, dry bag, straps for sunglasses Photos - we do our best to take pics during your trip and we send them to you free of charge Use of Lockable Area on Land
fields.what_to_bring: Sun hat, water, sunglasses, waterproof bag
fields.departure_location: Hondoq Bay, Qala, Malta. Take a left at the end of the winding road into the car park. You'll see a blue trailer and kayaks near the water
